Date: Mon, 31 May 2021 09:48:47 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] cmd/compile: add Tilde (OCOM) op, remove XOR unary

Using ^x in other languages causes an invalid compile
and throws a syntax error. To be more align with the
usage of the ~ unary op just like in other languages,
it's better to remove the use of ^x.

This commit renames OBITNOT OpCode to OCOM, since we
already use COM opcode in the assembly calls in order to
do bitwise not operations.

This commit includes a language change. And will not be
compiled successfully. The next commit will refactor
the all the ^x usages to ~x.

